  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Healing from Stress/Trauma</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project is raised to support Solidarity with South Sudan to organize training of trainers (ToT) workshops. Solidarity with SS Pastoral Services have given workshops in Healing from Stress/Trauma throughout South Sudan since 2009; for example, in Malakal, Juba, Bor, Duk, Bentiu, Yambio, Nzara, Yei, Wau, Rumbek, Molou, Maban, Torit, Agok/Abyei, in many Protection of Civilian Camps.  We also taught Psychosocial Support for two years for the Education in Emergencies Program throughout SS, and then supervised field work in some areas, and we incorpoarate it into our Teacher Training Programs.  Workshop participants represent a wide range of South Sudanese population, many tribes and various age ranges including children and elderly; for example, women&#x2019;s groups, men&#x2019;s groups, teachers, medical staffs, prisoners, the sick, homeless, special needs, youth, ecumenical/interfaith, staffs of organizations and some government personnel.</narrative>
  </description>
